The sign of $A_l$  is determined as sign$\left(A_l\right)=$ sign $\left[{\mathbf{{m}}}_i\cdot\left({\mathbf{{m}}}_j\times{\mathbf{{m}}}_k\right)\right]$.

The vertices $i$, $j$, $k$  of each elementary triangle are numbered in a counter-clockwise sense relative to the surface normal vector ${\mathbf{{n}}}$ pointing in positive direction of the $z$-axis.
The latter means that the numbering should satisfies the following condition ${\mathbf{{n}}}\cdot({\mathbf{{r}}}_{ij}\times {\mathbf{{r}}}_{ik})>0$, where ${\mathbf{{r}}}_{ij}$ is a connection vector directed from lattice site $i$ to $j$.

The parameter $a_l=A_l/4\pi$ can be thought as \textit{local topological charge}, which takes values in the range of $-0.5 < a_l < +0.5$.
