\section{Supplementary movie} \label{subsection_switching-video}

The movie shows the back and forth skyrmion switching by the sequence of magnetic field pulses of amplitude $B_\textrm{0}$ = 3 T and width $t_\textrm{w}$ = 15 ps with alternating polar angles $\theta=45^\circ$ and $\theta^\prime=135^\circ$. 
For the simulations in a square shape domain of $100 \times 100 \times 3$ spins, we have used the material parameters $J=5$~meV, $D/J=0.16$, $K/J=0.1$, $\alpha=0.1$ and OBC.
An interval of about 200 ps between two consecutive switching events suggests a skyrmion switching rate in the GHz range.
